replyContent: We're sorry you're seeing a problem with the app. Please contact support@aifactory.co.uk to help us understand what might be happening. If you are in a 2 player match, please use your device "back" button to leave the match, then choose "Single Player", set your preferred cpu level and tap "PLAY".

content: What the hell is this? I have intolerable views towards games like this. The AI ALWAYS win. The paid version still has ads.
replyContent: The AI does not always win. We create games to be fair and fun so that people will enjoy playing. The paid version has no ads and installs as a separate app. Please open "Reversi", not "Reversi Free". On first start-up it picks up stats from the free version if you have allowed stats recording in both apps.

content: Have play this game for years love it

I thought this was a different game at first,  thought it was the game of connecting 5 dots in a straight line to win.  However, this game turns out to be a game that I've always heard of people playing while I'm growing up,  but have never play it myself. I suppose there are many variations to this type of game, where you take over the opponent's piece by surrounding it with your own. Anyway,  it takes a while to get a hang of this game. But once I do, its very fun to play.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback. We also have Gomoku in the app store which sounds like the game you are describing.

replyContent: We're sorry you're experiencing a problem with the app. If this is still a problem, please try updating your Android version. We've had reports of Android version + device displaying this problem with apps of ours and other developers, and subsequent reports of the problem resolving once Android version is updated.
